Capital Markets

Company Overview of Fairfax Partners, LLC



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
William J. Atkins  Partner, Fairfax Partners, LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 0 Board Members in 0 different organizations across 3 different industries.55--
Background

		Mr. William J. Atkins is a Partner at Fairfax Partners, LLC. Mr. Atkins served as the Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President at Calix, Inc. since February 10, 2014 until May 19, 2017. He was a Senior Partner at Fairfax Media Partners, LLC. At Fairfax, he has advised media and telecommunications companies on, inter alia, the monetization of their assets and on their overall positioning and internal readiness for investor exits via either initial public offerings ... or strategic sales. He served as the Chief Financial Officer at two telecommunications companies.  Prior to Fairfax, Mr. Atkins served as the Chief Financial Officer at Rivada Networks International, LLC from 2006 to 2009 and also served as its Executive Vice President. At Rivada Networks International, he prepared it for further rounds of fund-raising, including the establishment of budgets and long-term plans. Mr. Atkins instituted financial controls and prepared Rivada Networks International for its first audit by a Big 4 accounting firm. From March 2004 to June 2005, he served as the Chief Financial Officer of Intelsat Investments S.A. and also served as its Executive Vice President from May 2004 to June 2005. At the firm, Mr. Atkins led the $5.1 billion private equity sale process, including associated investor presentations, valuations, reviews of strategic alternatives and negotiations with the ultimate owners of the business. Within the firm, he instituted centralized monthly reporting, introduced rolling twelve month forecasting, created product line based profitability analyses, established Sarbanes-Oxley compliance readiness and initiated the overhaul of previously fragmented and inefficient accounting systems and procedures. Prior to joining Intelsat, he was a senior member of Morgan Stanley’s Investment Banking Division and held various positions from 1994 to 2003, including Head of European Corporate Finance Execution, Deputy Head of Investment Banking in Japan and Head of European Telecommunications Corporate Finance. He served as Managing Director and Senior Member at Morgan Stanley from December 1994 to October 2003. In that time, Mr. Atkins also served as Group Head of the Corporate Finance Execution Group at Morgan Stanley from November 2001 to October 2003 and as Deputy Head of the Investment Banking Division from January 2001 to November 2002 and has executed over $100 billion of mergers and acquisitions, restructurings, IPOs and equity and debt financings, primarily in the telecoms and media sector. Prior to Morgan Stanley, he co-founded the Telecommunications Investment Banking practice at S.G. Warburg, where worked from 1985 to 1994. He has also served an Adviser to plaintiffs’ attorneys on valuation issues related to litigation in the telecoms equipment sector. Mr. Atkins has both operational and banking expertise. His involvement in the telecommunications and media sectors spans two decades, ranging from the privatization of formerly government controlled operators, through the funding of new wireless and alternative carriers in response to industry deregulation and technological change and to executing both as principal and advisor mergers, acquisitions, divestitures and public and private debt and equity offerings with an aggregate transaction value of over $100 billion. He serves as Treasurer and Board member of the Ellington Fund. Mr. Atkins has earned an M.A. and a B.A. from Stanford University.Read Full Background




